647
00:57:10,101 --> 00:57:13,541
Public participation petition to the Honorable City Council.

648
00:57:14,962 --> 00:57:16,162
Citizens participation.

649
00:57:17,937 --> 00:57:24,899
offered by Robert M. Penta that the issue of water and sewer base be charged since 2017 be discussed.

650
00:57:26,259 --> 00:57:27,760
Good evening, name and address of the record, please.

651
00:57:27,780 --> 00:57:30,100
My name is Robert Penta, Zero Summit Road.

652
00:57:30,120 --> 00:57:31,901
I don't know if you can hear me.

653
00:57:32,061 --> 00:57:33,201
We'd appreciate it if you don't touch that.

654
00:57:33,481 --> 00:57:35,442
No, can you hear it?

655
00:57:35,562 --> 00:57:36,922
Can you hear me?

656
00:57:36,982 --> 00:57:37,923
Yes, we can hear you.

657
00:57:38,763 --> 00:57:46,725
Back in May of 2017, what was presented here before the city of Method was a new, what they call a base,

658
00:57:47,498 --> 00:57:50,539
rate of 861 per household.

659
00:57:50,979 --> 00:57:58,002
And then the different charge would be for the commercial district folks here in the city of Medford.

660
00:57:58,622 --> 00:58:03,364
And then one of the arguments was that it would raise $1 million a year.

661
00:58:03,384 --> 00:58:10,786
That was approximately 4% of what the city's budget was at that point in time required for the water and sewer services in the city of Medford.

662
00:58:11,807 --> 00:58:15,268
Subsequent to that, it's gone on for the last three years.

663
00:58:16,000 --> 00:58:17,881
now coming into its fourth fiscal year.

664
00:58:18,821 --> 00:58:32,945
And I believe a response that was sent back to the city, you folks, pursuant to a request from one of your colleagues, was a breakdown of how much money each and every one of the last three fiscal years amounted to.

665
00:58:33,945 --> 00:58:43,128
Inclusive of that amount, again, was the term of $1 million to be used per year, but they never reached the $1 million per year.

666
00:58:44,563 --> 00:58:57,951
What was reached was $2,585,362.66 as compared to the $3 million that was allegedly stated that the city would gain.

667
00:58:58,411 --> 00:58:59,351
That's a difference of $414,637.

668
00:58:59,612 --> 00:59:04,274
So where do we go with that?

669
00:59:04,875 --> 00:59:14,140
Where we go with that, the argument was that that would be used to supplement water and sewer for whatever needs might be if something were to come up

670
00:59:14,937 --> 00:59:20,601
also to subsidize the water and sewer department in case of something that's anticipated.

671
00:59:21,501 --> 00:59:33,749
In the letter that came back, it indicated here that the universal connectivity fee is an infrastructure recovery charge to be hooked into and maintained in the water and sewer system.

672
00:59:34,349 --> 00:59:43,475
The fixed base connectivity fee is estimated at $1 million per year to help stabilize revenues in this place.

673
00:59:44,439 --> 00:59:49,161
That response also indicated that that money goes to your water and sewer account.

674
00:59:50,161 --> 00:59:51,502
There is no breakdown.

675
00:59:52,182 --> 00:59:56,504
There is no breakdown to the charges, commercial or residential.

676
00:59:57,084 --> 01:00:01,566
There is no breakdown also as to how and where that money has been spent.

677
01:00:02,127 --> 01:00:07,729
And there is no program that is set up presently that tells you what that money can be used for.

678
01:00:08,149 --> 01:00:12,011
So right now, all it's done has been included into your water and sewer account.

679
01:00:12,957 --> 01:00:25,164
One of the misnomers to this whole project, when sold back in 2017, was in case there is a, in case, that's the word, in case there is a deficit in either the water or sewer account.

680
01:00:25,904 --> 01:00:31,287
In the years 2016 and 17, there were deficits on the sewer side, not the water side.

681
01:00:32,428 --> 01:00:40,292
But each and every year, when the water and sewer budget is estimated, it's estimated on what the work is going to be here in the city of Method, and also,

682
01:00:40,852 --> 01:00:48,336
The water and the sewer rates that you get from the MWRA, those rates come in ahead of time, not after a budget is made and set.

683
01:00:48,896 --> 01:00:51,458
That's another misnomer as it relates to the full program.

684
01:00:52,118 --> 01:01:10,148
So approximately right now, you're sitting on $2,585,000 of base rate fees or charges, whatever the term you want to use, that has come from the Mr. and Mrs. Metro taxpayer has been put into the general revenues of your water and sewer account.

685
01:01:11,140 --> 01:01:20,684
That ladies and gentlemen is not the proper accounting practices and procedures because in your own water and sewer account, you have to have it broken down.

686
01:01:21,064 --> 01:01:22,845
You have it broken down by employees.

687
01:01:23,185 --> 01:01:25,266
You have it broken down by cost of material.

688
01:01:25,586 --> 01:01:30,268
You have it broken down by the named individuals in the trucks and everything else that goes along with it.

689
01:01:31,309 --> 01:01:33,950
My suggestion to you folks would be simply this.

690
01:01:35,231 --> 01:01:38,132
You can't put a fee on somebody or a charge

691
01:01:38,987 --> 01:01:41,288
without knowing what you're charging them for.

692
01:01:42,228 --> 01:01:42,988
It's not fair.

693
01:01:43,429 --> 01:01:50,071
If that's the case, you should have just raised the water and sewer account by the approximate 4% that you think it was going to do to offset it.

694
01:01:51,031 --> 01:02:06,517
So if you're sitting on a surplus of approximately $7 million or thereabouts in your water and sewer enterprise account, and you're sitting on approximately having already raised $2.5 million, but you still don't know how it was spent, where it was gonna go,

695
01:02:07,116 --> 01:02:09,377
Where is the projected projects that are supposed to come?

696
01:02:10,238 --> 01:02:15,361
It doesn't make any sense because right now, what it's saying is it's a water and sewage charge.

697
01:02:15,881 --> 01:02:19,903
It was to services in case something were to happen.

698
01:02:20,984 --> 01:02:26,287
The original proposal back in 2017 was the charge for the water meeting.

699
01:02:26,607 --> 01:02:30,289
And that was the charge that was going to be placed on each and every residential person.

700
01:02:31,270 --> 01:02:35,392
So we know right now that that charge every single time, once it comes out,

701
01:02:36,162 --> 01:02:37,122
is not for the meter.

702
01:02:37,642 --> 01:02:48,725
But unfortunately, for accounting purposes, because you can't figure it out, in this city, in the accounting department, there is nothing to be found that'll tell you how and where that money was spent.

703
01:02:49,145 --> 01:02:53,586
But you can find it in water and sewer, in their particular budgets, independently separated.

704
01:02:54,806 --> 01:02:58,487
My suggestion would be to you, that you have a budget coming up this year.

705
01:02:59,067 --> 01:03:04,088
I would hope that maybe somebody would make a request and ask the question, because it doesn't make any sense

706
01:03:04,759 --> 01:03:09,281
that the response that came back from the finance director, we don't keep an accounting.

707
01:03:09,882 --> 01:03:18,887
Well, if you don't keep an accounting, how do you keep an accounting of residential and commercial meters that you have and what you're going to be charged?

708
01:03:19,367 --> 01:03:24,270
How can you allege that you're going to be taking in a million dollars a year when you haven't even got to that figure?

709
01:03:26,171 --> 01:03:30,773
Something needs to be said as it relates to these type of budgetary items.

710
01:03:30,813 --> 01:03:34,035
Seven weeks ago, I came in here and I think I explained something like seven items.

711
01:03:34,810 --> 01:03:37,712
I'm going to go through them all one at a time, not tonight, Mr. President.

712
01:03:38,232 --> 01:03:39,653
I will go through them all one at a time.

713
01:03:40,374 --> 01:03:46,638
Because good accounting procedures tells you what comes in has got to go out and how does it go out.

714
01:03:47,579 --> 01:03:57,645
You've got situations here that you really don't know why should you be charging these people to supplement or augment a water and sewer account that's presently sitting in millions of dollars.

715
01:03:58,106 --> 01:04:03,169
You have yet to be told what the cost is going to be for an anticipated construction

716
01:04:03,756 --> 01:04:07,838
sidewalk, street reconstruction might be because of water and sewer.

717
01:04:08,278 --> 01:04:13,500
So if you keep taking in these monies from Mr. and Mrs. Taxpayer, you're overcharging them.

718
01:04:14,061 --> 01:04:19,083
You're overcharging them each and every year on this base rate, the speed, whatever it might be.

719
01:04:19,123 --> 01:04:20,183
Point of information, Mr. President.

720
01:04:20,203 --> 01:04:21,724
Point of information, Vice President Knight.

721
01:04:21,804 --> 01:04:30,588
I think it's important to point out, and I understand what the council is saying, and I don't want to interrupt them, but I think it's important to point out that this base fee is something that's implemented by the administration.

722
01:04:31,358 --> 01:04:34,859
It's not a vote that was taken by the council, does not require council approval.

723
01:04:35,059 --> 01:04:36,880
It's under the purview of the Water and Sewer Commission.

724
01:04:36,960 --> 01:04:38,700
They meet monthly to discuss these type of items.

725
01:04:39,621 --> 01:04:49,064
And that the accounting that's being done should be done in accord with the GAA, the Government Accounting Office, the General Accepted Accounting Principles, Mr. President.

726
01:04:50,004 --> 01:04:56,666
And looking at what the gentleman's saying, I do have some agreement with what he's saying, but there's also some items that we need to clarify.

727
01:04:56,706 --> 01:04:59,407
And the first item we need to clarify is this is the doing of the council.

728
01:04:59,971 --> 01:05:01,992
This is the doing of the administration of the Water and Sewer Commission.

729
01:05:04,033 --> 01:05:08,255
Well, while that may be true, there's also, you talk about general accounting practices.

730
01:05:08,295 --> 01:05:28,325
General accounting practices does state that if you are going to put a budgetary item on a budget, as you councilors get each and every year, the question needs to be asked, if I'm going to just put $100 million, so to speak, and put it into a line item, and there's no accounting of the money, other than the fact I just put it into an account, what's the purpose of that?

731
01:05:29,019 --> 01:05:40,589
So you're right, it's an administrative prerogative, but when it came up in May of 2017, it was contentiously argued at this Memphis City Council as to why we need this new fee.

732
01:05:40,910 --> 01:05:46,955
And at that point in time, the argument was for the purposes of the meters, for the accounting of the meters.

733
01:05:47,015 --> 01:05:54,501
Now it's going into the general revenue, and now we're being told that there is no delineation, there's no explanation, there's no accounting of how that money's being spent.

734
01:05:55,202 --> 01:05:56,123
So if that's the case,

735
01:05:56,607 --> 01:06:04,329
And as counselors, if there's no explanation of how it's being spent, before you used to have the accounting firm of Melanson and Heath, you don't have them anymore.

736
01:06:04,609 --> 01:06:06,529
You have them for like 15 years out of New Hampshire.

737
01:06:06,809 --> 01:06:10,370
You have a new accounting company that comes in here, they're supposed to do an annual audit.

738
01:06:10,730 --> 01:06:11,810
That question ought to come up.

739
01:06:12,050 --> 01:06:25,013
Because if you remember correctly, if you looked at the Melanson and Heath audits, that was one of their concerns on the MWRA, especially in our water and sewer accounts, if you go back and read them, the accounting and the prioritizing how the money is spent.

740
01:06:25,946 --> 01:06:30,169
This account, or this money, Councilor Knight, there's no accounting with the money.

741
01:06:30,329 --> 01:06:32,211
It just goes into a general revenue.

742
01:06:32,271 --> 01:06:34,493
I didn't say you didn't have legitimate concerns, Councilor Pinto.

743
01:06:34,513 --> 01:06:41,098
What I said was that it needs to be pointed out that the Memphis City Council isn't the one that implemented these fees, and Memphis City Council isn't the one that has the purview to remove them.

744
01:06:43,380 --> 01:06:48,484
As watchdogs of the city's money, over and beyond the administration, the administration can make a proposal.

745
01:06:48,924 --> 01:06:50,305
The bottom line is here with the council.

746
01:06:50,325 --> 01:06:51,746
You either vote it up or you vote it down.

747
01:06:52,187 --> 01:06:53,788
And if you're going to vote it up or you're going to vote it down,

748
01:06:54,161 --> 01:06:55,902
The question is, what are you voting on?

749
01:06:56,222 --> 01:07:03,484
And if something comes to your attention to be questioned as to why and how, this is where it's going to take place in the Memphis City Council Chambers.

750
01:07:04,864 --> 01:07:09,846
But the matter is never going to come before us for us to vote up or down because it is not within our purview.

751
01:07:09,866 --> 01:07:11,726
It is within the purview of the Water and Sewer Commission.

752
01:07:11,746 --> 01:07:14,227
So the beef is not here in the Alden Chambers.

753
01:07:14,507 --> 01:07:16,388
It should be in room 201 with the Water and Sewer Commission.

754
01:07:18,148 --> 01:07:23,650
Then I would respectfully suggest, if we follow that train of thought, I would respectfully suggest a freedom of information

755
01:07:24,300 --> 01:07:29,961
request to the city auditor, asking the city auditor.

756
01:07:30,681 --> 01:07:36,102
As to why, Mr. President, why there is no accounting.

757
01:07:36,362 --> 01:07:43,404
When you get the money from the MWRA ahead of time, before a budget is made, there's an accounting of how that money is going to be spent.

758
01:07:43,964 --> 01:07:44,504
You have money.

759
01:07:44,524 --> 01:07:45,984
What information, Mr. President?

760
01:07:46,504 --> 01:07:47,925
What information, Councilor Biss?

761
01:07:48,425 --> 01:07:51,466
Just, it's a public records request, not a freedom of information.

762
01:07:51,706 --> 01:07:52,066
Thank you.

763
01:07:53,166 --> 01:07:53,806
Thank you, Councilor Biss.

764
01:07:54,577 --> 01:07:58,559
I believe, Mr. President, a Freedom of Information Act can come from anybody.

765
01:07:58,579 --> 01:08:05,902
And if the council does not get it as you got it from the response from the finance person, then you would go to that next group.

766
01:08:06,182 --> 01:08:13,505
Because again, if you follow what Councilor Neider said, if allegedly it comes from the Water and Soil Commission, it's their call, maybe their call to implement it.

767
01:08:13,805 --> 01:08:17,567
But it's your call to decide how and where, if it's going to be spent.

768
01:08:17,727 --> 01:08:21,589
And you guys can ask for an accounting of how the money is being spent.

769
01:08:23,810 --> 01:08:24,130
That's it.

770
01:08:24,487 --> 01:08:24,787
Thank you.

771
01:08:24,807 --> 01:08:36,951
You're more than happy to answer the questions because it's the finances of our community and you can't keep tagging on to Mr. and Mrs. Taxpayer and now not having an answer or an explanation.

772
01:08:37,452 --> 01:08:39,252
Mr. President, Councilor Baxton.

773
01:08:40,373 --> 01:08:43,234
I wanna thank my former council colleague.

774
01:08:44,054 --> 01:08:52,717
I know he's very passionate on this and this is not the first time Councilor Penta spoke on this issue and he does raise some valid concerns.

775
01:08:53,662 --> 01:09:03,126
I offered the resolution back some several weeks ago and read thoroughly the response we got from Alicia Nunley, our finance director.

776
01:09:03,607 --> 01:09:15,572
And I also received the correspondence via email from the Water and Sewer Commission to the chair, Dominic Camara, who in my opinion, along with the rest of the board,

777
01:09:16,018 --> 01:09:23,401
is doing a great job in a very difficult, as you can imagine, board to operate, Mr. President.

778
01:09:24,062 --> 01:09:37,488
And, you know, the response that we received from the administration, we did ask this council ask directly, if we're able to see the base rate, what that actually pays for within the water and sewer enterprise account.

779
01:09:38,208 --> 01:09:44,331
And they were unable to break out that particular portion compared to just the regular rates

780
01:09:44,784 --> 01:09:50,866
and say, well, with the base rate, we paid for X, Y, and Z. And that's how they do their accounting.

781
01:09:50,966 --> 01:09:53,287
And personally, I don't see a problem with that.

782
01:09:53,927 --> 01:10:01,890
What Councilor Penter is asking for is more of an itemized type listing of where the expenditures are going based on what

783
01:10:02,462 --> 01:10:08,965
revenues coming in, and I'm not sure if they have the capability or capacity to report it out that way.

784
01:10:09,466 --> 01:10:14,228
But that, as Councilor Knight mentioned, that's not really end of our purview anyways.

785
01:10:15,289 --> 01:10:24,633
When this originally came out on the council, there was some concern because members of the council, including myself, thought this was a connectivity fee.

786
01:10:25,214 --> 01:10:31,517
And it raised a lot of eyebrows because at the time we said, wait a minute, we usually have a surplus in the water and sewer accounts,

787
01:10:32,010 --> 01:10:39,099
of several million dollars, why would we need now all of a sudden start charging residents a connectivity fee?

788
01:10:39,379 --> 01:10:41,962
We're already connected to the water and sewer system.

789
01:10:43,103 --> 01:10:47,949
But come to find out it wasn't really a connectivity fee, it was a base rate fee.

790
01:10:48,510 --> 01:10:50,913
And there is a difference, a substantial difference.

791
01:10:51,573 --> 01:10:56,298
And as Councilor Pinto alluded to, the base fee is a stabilizer.

792
01:10:56,818 --> 01:11:06,247
So the way it was told to me and the way I understand it is that every period, the billing period, we're not sure what we're going to receive for revenue.

793
01:11:07,019 --> 01:11:11,580
We know how much the MWRE is going to charge us because we have everything needed, right?

794
01:11:12,340 --> 01:11:19,022
City Hall gets constant updates through the little antenna on your water meter telling how much the water usage is.

795
01:11:19,382 --> 01:11:23,723
So City Hall at any given minute could say how much the water consumption is.

796
01:11:24,123 --> 01:11:31,045
We have giant meters throughout the community that show the inflow and outflow of sewage.

797
01:11:31,585 --> 01:11:34,806
And we can tell you how much sewage is leaving this community.

798
01:11:35,166 --> 01:11:36,786
So they have a good handle on

799
01:11:37,565 --> 01:11:41,327
what the fixed charges are in this community.

800
01:11:41,667 --> 01:11:46,509
The handle we don't have is how much revenue are we gonna bring in?

801
01:11:46,949 --> 01:11:55,352
Because there may be, especially during these fiscal difficult times during COVID, that someone may not be able to pay their water and sewer bill.

802
01:11:55,952 --> 01:11:58,613
And it happens not just during COVID, other times.

803
01:11:59,774 --> 01:12:03,455
And so having, the way I understand it, a base rate set up

804
01:12:04,553 --> 01:12:06,714
It sets up a revenue stabilizer.

805
01:12:06,754 --> 01:12:14,000
So we know there's a million dollars guarantee that's coming from the rate payers that's gonna pay off what we owe.

806
01:12:14,941 --> 01:12:16,523
So it's not an extra charge.

807
01:12:17,043 --> 01:12:19,365
It is definitely not an extra charge in the bill.

808
01:12:19,685 --> 01:12:24,890
It goes towards paying off your rate, the water and sewer rate for the entire community.

809
01:12:25,370 --> 01:12:27,572
And it's somewhat provides a stabilizer.

810
01:12:28,272 --> 01:12:30,074
One would ask, why don't we raise it?

811
01:12:30,581 --> 01:12:32,963
because the million dollars is not much of a stabilizer.

812
01:12:33,224 --> 01:12:34,645
Why don't we raise that base fee?

813
01:12:35,005 --> 01:12:42,713
And then we can have guaranteed money in there and know where the money's coming from and serve the same purpose.

814
01:12:43,213 --> 01:12:46,356
So I think I understand where you're coming from councilor.

815
01:12:46,877 --> 01:12:51,441
I'm not quite sure the city has the capability of providing that level of detail.

816
01:12:51,908 --> 01:12:57,833
that you're looking for regarding what projects were done in the city, what infrastructure did this money go towards?

817
01:12:58,653 --> 01:12:59,294
Leak detection.

818
01:12:59,314 --> 01:13:01,635
You've been talking about leak detection for 20 years.

819
01:13:02,316 --> 01:13:08,541
We have a high percentage of water that's leaking out throughout the system, and it's costing the rate payers millions of dollars.

820
01:13:08,881 --> 01:13:12,664
The council has probably heard me a million times about inflow and infiltration.

821
01:13:12,984 --> 01:13:13,785
The sewer system.

822
01:13:14,305 --> 01:13:20,770
We accept groundwater that's going into the sewer system, and that groundwater is going out to Deer Island and being treated as raw sewage.

823
01:13:21,487 --> 01:13:23,268
costing us millions of dollars a year.

824
01:13:24,189 --> 01:13:26,190
And we're aware of it, but guess what?

825
01:13:26,230 --> 01:13:28,152
We have an aging infrastructure.

826
01:13:28,512 --> 01:13:30,514
You know, so this is a much larger issue.

827
01:13:31,174 --> 01:13:33,436
I wanna thank the council for keeping it in front of us.

828
01:13:33,916 --> 01:13:48,627
You know, our water meters, like the new schools that we talk about that were put in 17 years ago, our water meters are now, the new water meters are 15 to 17 years old, and the life expectancy was roughly 13 to 15 years.

829
01:13:49,207 --> 01:13:50,428
And it's just a matter of time

830
01:13:50,822 --> 01:13:56,483
that we experienced when I first got on the council, that half of our meters were being estimated.

