1049
01:29:39,892 --> 01:29:47,419
capital plan to reflect the resurfacing of city roads and the revitalization of Memphis Square and Mystic Avenue as year one priorities.

1050
01:29:47,439 --> 01:29:54,986
And be it further resolved, the capital plan be adjusted to call for a resurfacing of no less than 10 miles of roadway per year.

1051
01:29:55,026 --> 01:29:55,767
Vice President Knight.

1052
01:29:56,027 --> 01:29:57,708
Mr. President, thank you very much.

1053
01:29:58,509 --> 01:30:00,251
Here in the city of Memphis, we have about 140 miles of roadway.

1054
01:30:02,395 --> 01:30:09,401
And if we look at the capital plan that was released last week, I had the opportunity to watch the meeting on local access television.

1055
01:30:09,421 --> 01:30:12,723
Pat Gordon did a good job delivering that TV program to us last week.

1056
01:30:13,484 --> 01:30:23,072
If you look at the capital plan, you'll see that over a six-year period, it calls for the resurfacing of about 11 roads, Mr. President.

1057
01:30:23,632 --> 01:30:31,038
Now, we're a community that has 145 miles of roadway, and I don't think there's one street in this community at this point in time that's

1058
01:30:31,672 --> 01:30:38,495
pristinely paved from curb to curb with no potholes, no markings, no proper markings and signage, proper crosswalks and the like.

1059
01:30:40,016 --> 01:30:52,102
Everybody in this community uses roads to get from point A to point B, whether it be school buses, fire engines, plows, police cars, you and me, bicycles, pedestrians, everybody uses the streets, Mr. President.

1060
01:30:52,822 --> 01:30:56,444
And the condition of our roadways at this point in time are subpar.

1061
01:30:57,004 --> 01:30:59,966
When you look at surrounding communities, you can tell when you get there.

1062
01:31:01,034 --> 01:31:02,255
because the pavement changes.

1063
01:31:02,855 --> 01:31:06,017
When you drive from Bedford into Malden, all of a sudden the ride gets a little less bumpy.

1064
01:31:06,638 --> 01:31:08,859
The same thing when you go into Arlington or Somerville or Winchester.

1065
01:31:09,499 --> 01:31:11,160
So Mr. President, we have a capital plan.

1066
01:31:11,321 --> 01:31:14,703
We've heard a lot about this pavement inventory that was going to be taken by the administration.

1067
01:31:16,364 --> 01:31:21,087
Ultimately at this point in time, you know, the curb appeal in this community isn't what it once was.

1068
01:31:21,787 --> 01:31:25,890
And we need to start investing money back in our infrastructure so that our curb appeal

1069
01:31:26,758 --> 01:31:32,483
can be something that's enticing, so that a curb appeal can be something that when a taxpayer looks out their window, they can be proud of.

1070
01:31:33,064 --> 01:31:37,789
Instead of having to call C-Click fix, they can smile and tell their friends, why don't you come over and take a look at what a great job they did.

1071
01:31:38,429 --> 01:31:43,674
I will say this, the plowing that's been done in the community over the past year or so has been excellent, Mr. President.

1072
01:31:44,375 --> 01:31:49,720
But with that being said, the toll that's taken on our roads is beginning to show.

1073
01:31:50,610 --> 01:31:56,415
So with that being said, I'm requesting that the administration adjust the capital plan to take into consideration our aging infrastructure and roadways.

1074
01:31:58,317 --> 01:32:02,801
With 10 miles a year, it would still take us 14 years to resurface each roadway in the community.

1075
01:32:04,142 --> 01:32:10,067
So it's an ambitious goal, Mr. President, but I feel as though we need to do something more ambitious than 12 streets over six years.

1076
01:32:11,569 --> 01:32:16,093
That coupled with the fact that we've been talking about ways to generate revenue in this community, to generate new growth,

1077
01:32:16,748 --> 01:32:18,930
to address the $5 to $8 million budget deficit.

1078
01:32:19,610 --> 01:32:25,974
We've been discussing the revitalization of Method Square now since the 100-year parade when I was in the fifth grade.

1079
01:32:26,635 --> 01:32:30,797
And we had a great opportunity to address some concerns along Mystic Gap.

1080
01:32:31,338 --> 01:32:36,421
And I think that that's kind of fallen by the wayside after all the work that the Metropolitan Area Planning Council has done.

1081
01:32:36,921 --> 01:32:39,703
I'm very happy of the work that we've been able to do with Mr. Barbrowski.

1082
01:32:40,164 --> 01:32:43,586
And once we get this recodification process

1083
01:32:44,180 --> 01:32:50,184
completed, I look forward to moving forward and hopefully securing the zoning consultant for further review of our zoning ordinances.

1084
01:32:50,785 --> 01:32:54,187
But with that being said, Mr. President, I asked my council colleagues to support this resolution.

1085
01:32:54,787 --> 01:32:58,790
I feel as though it's a capital plan that needs to invest in things that matter.

1086
01:32:59,331 --> 01:33:01,912
And one thing that everybody in this community uses is our roads.

1087
01:33:03,874 --> 01:33:06,456
So with that being said, I'd ask my council colleagues to support the resolution.

1088
01:33:06,716 --> 01:33:07,516
Thank you, Mr. Vice President.

1089
01:33:07,536 --> 01:33:08,097
Councilor Baez.

1090
01:33:08,857 --> 01:33:09,638
Thank you, Mr. President.

1091
01:33:09,698 --> 01:33:12,620
I agree with Councilor Knight's sentiment and I will be supporting the resolution.

1092
01:33:13,155 --> 01:33:26,186
I'd just like to propose a B paper that also asks how many miles would be resurfaced per year under the initial proposal from the administration?

1093
01:33:28,868 --> 01:33:34,112
Yes, how many miles per year proposed under the initial capital plan draft?

1094
01:33:34,953 --> 01:33:36,114
Thank you, Mr. President.

1095
01:33:36,214 --> 01:33:40,217
I want to thank Vice President Knight for bringing this up.

1096
01:33:42,178 --> 01:33:47,781
I think behind this rail, we've all spoken about sidewalks and roads ad nauseum.

1097
01:33:48,461 --> 01:33:52,603
And I think this is a great proposal.

1098
01:33:53,124 --> 01:34:02,829
However, Mr. President, with that being said, we as a council have not had the opportunity to sit down as a council and go over the capital plan.

1099
01:34:03,429 --> 01:34:10,133
And I would respectfully ask my colleague to hold off on this until we have the ability as a council to sit down

1100
01:34:10,718 --> 01:34:18,823
and go through what we believe are some of the issues that we would like to see addressed within the capital plan and not do it piecemeal.

1101
01:34:19,424 --> 01:34:30,911
And I would just respectfully ask my council colleague to either withdraw this or set up a meeting where we can sit down and have a meaningful dialogue.

1102
01:34:30,971 --> 01:34:32,852
It's $107 million proposal.

1103
01:34:33,453 --> 01:34:36,915
And I also had the opportunity to watch it, Mr. President.

1104
01:34:37,255 --> 01:34:39,817
And there are a lot of unanswered questions

1105
01:34:40,277 --> 01:34:50,235
from the school appropriation to when the fire department will eventually see their buildings be refurbished and why are we waiting so long to refurbish?

1106
01:34:50,605 --> 01:34:55,407
the fire headquarters, as well as the other existing buildings.

1107
01:34:55,787 --> 01:34:57,988
I think there's a lot that needs to go over.

1108
01:34:58,548 --> 01:35:04,671
And I don't want to send a message that if we do support this, that this is what the council is looking for.

1109
01:35:05,111 --> 01:35:10,733
And that's it, Mr. President, because that's furthest from I as one member of the council.

1110
01:35:10,773 --> 01:35:14,275
So I hope my council colleague can appreciate that.

1111
01:35:14,315 --> 01:35:19,017
And maybe we can use this as a catalyst to take a look at the capital plan

1112
01:35:19,538 --> 01:35:23,579
and see what the needs are as a council and as a community.

1113
01:35:23,639 --> 01:35:25,179
The way I look at it, Mr. President, is this.

1114
01:35:25,279 --> 01:35:26,460
The plan's been released.

1115
01:35:26,660 --> 01:35:27,460
The plan is the plan.

1116
01:35:27,660 --> 01:35:31,421
The mayor didn't involve us in the planning procedure, in the planning process.

1117
01:35:32,221 --> 01:35:40,283
This council, week in and week out, sends the administration requests in the form of resolutions, making requests and recommendations as to where money should be invested.

1118
01:35:41,963 --> 01:35:45,264
This proposal right here falls in line with the votes that the council's taken in the past.

1119
01:35:45,957 --> 01:35:49,039
I understand where he's coming from, but I respectfully decline.

1120
01:35:49,079 --> 01:35:50,700
I'd like to have the paper be voted on, Mr. President.

1121
01:35:50,720 --> 01:35:52,561
I'd like to see the capital plan addressed.

1122
01:35:52,641 --> 01:35:54,402
I've had enough of the condition of these roadways.

1123
01:35:54,702 --> 01:36:02,326
I've been banging on this table since I got elected, talking about public utilities coming in this community, tearing up our streets, about what we're gonna do to come up with a plan.

1124
01:36:02,346 --> 01:36:04,868
And we're not getting anywhere.

1125
01:36:05,068 --> 01:36:06,909
Now we have a capital investment plan, Mr. President.

1126
01:36:06,929 --> 01:36:08,750
We have a CIP and it doesn't address our streets.

1127
01:36:10,291 --> 01:36:12,652
So if the council is taking these votes and we're serious about the votes we've taken,

1128
01:36:13,433 --> 01:36:15,534
And there are many other items that are going to be priorities.

1129
01:36:15,614 --> 01:36:18,335
I certainly don't feel as though that's an incorrect statement to make.

1130
01:36:18,715 --> 01:36:24,238
And I certainly understand that Councilor Marks has some priorities that he's fighting for as does Councilor Scott Kelly and so Councilor Falco.

1131
01:36:24,398 --> 01:36:31,721
But with that being said, Mr. President, the paper that's before us is to ask that the capital plan be adjusted to call for these things as year one priorities.

1132
01:36:32,461 --> 01:36:34,822
Any further putting it off is going to put us into year two.

1133
01:36:34,842 --> 01:36:36,082
There won't be year one priorities.

1134
01:36:36,863 --> 01:36:38,964
So with that being said, I'd ask my colleagues to support the paper.

1135
01:36:40,498 --> 01:36:41,558
It is what it is, Mr. President.

1136
01:36:42,078 --> 01:36:43,058
The mayor released the plan.

1137
01:36:43,278 --> 01:36:44,899
We asked for an opportunity to have involvement.

1138
01:36:45,519 --> 01:36:47,599
That opportunity wasn't afforded or awarded to us.

1139
01:36:47,739 --> 01:36:53,120
So now we gotta do what we gotta do to get in there what we think is important for our constituents in this community.

1140
01:36:53,400 --> 01:36:55,521
This is the approach I'd like to take in doing it, Mr. President.

1141
01:36:55,541 --> 01:37:00,301
I'd like to be put on record knowing that I support resurfacing of our roadways.

1142
01:37:00,421 --> 01:37:02,202
Again, it's something that everybody in this community uses.

1143
01:37:02,602 --> 01:37:03,942
It's something that everybody in this community needs.

1144
01:37:04,502 --> 01:37:06,542
And the quality there right now is awful.

1145
01:37:07,082 --> 01:37:10,223
So with that being said, I respectfully decline the gentleman's request

1146
01:37:10,646 --> 01:37:11,767
at this point in time, I feel.

1147
01:37:11,807 --> 01:37:13,710
Mr. President, if I could.

1148
01:37:14,791 --> 01:37:25,483
As I stated, I don't think anyone's been a bigger advocate of roads over my term on the council in discussing the needs and the fact that we don't put any money in the budget for roads.

1149
01:37:26,384 --> 01:37:31,850
From what I've been told by the mayor, and the mayor can correct me if I'm wrong, she told me this was a draft capital plan.

